.Dd $Mdocdate: April 5 2025 $
.Dt SYSCTL.CONF 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sysctl.conf
.Nd sysctl variables to set at system startup
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is made up of
.Xr sysctl 8
variable assignments
.Pq Ar variable Ns = Ns Ar value
with comments designated by a hash mark
.Pq Sq # .
.Pp
.Pa /etc/sysctl.conf
is read at system startup by
.Xr rc 8
early on in the boot sequence.
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width /etc/examples/sysctl.conf -compact
.It Pa /etc/sysctl.conf
.It Pa /etc/examples/sysctl.conf
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
To turn on IP forwarding, one would use the following line:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
net.inet.ip.forwarding=1
.Ed
.Pp
To cause the kernel to reboot on a panic, instead of dropping into
the debugger, the following can be used:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
ddb.panic=0
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sysctl 2 ,
.Xr rc 8 ,
.Xr sysctl 8
.Sh HISTORY
